<h1>Problem 222 - 2008 China TST Day 1, P3 of 3</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Suppose that every positive integer has been given one of the colours red, blue, arbitrarily. Prove that there exists an infinite sequence of positive integers \(a_{1} < a_{2} < a_{3} < \cdots < a_{n} < \cdots,\) such that the infinite sequence of positive integers \(a_{1},\frac{a_{1} + a_{2}}{2},a_{2},\frac{a_{2} + a_{3}}{2},a_{3},\frac{a_{3} + a_{4}}{2},\cdots\) has the same colour.</p>
